race.comment: THE BEAR (4) had gotten better with each run this time in and that culminated with a solid victory at this track last time out. Gets 2kg off with the claim and can play a role in the finish. RUINS OF ROME (1) boasts a win and a placing from two outings here and will be ready to peak now fourth-up from the break. In the mix. The well-related WILD GYPSY (6) (half to G1 winner Wild Ruler) is yet to miss a place in three starts over this distance range and may earn some minor money. ROCHEDALE HERO (5) draws the inside marble and will give backers a sight. SOUTHERN CHARM (3) will be rock-hard fit for this and can feature with any luck in running.
